---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '24 January 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Learn how TopoStory collects, uses, and protects your personal information."
>
  <section class="pt-12 pb-8 bg-terrain-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-display font-bold text-terrain-900">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-terrain-700">
        Last updated: {lastUpdated}
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose prose-terrain max-w-none">
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-terrain-900 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed">
              TopoStory ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy.
              This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard
              your information when you use our trail map creation service at topostory.com
              and app.topostory.com.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-terrain-900 mb-4">Information We Collect</h2>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-terrain-800 mt-6 mb-3">Account Information</h3>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              When you create an account, we collect:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-terrain-700 space-y-2">
              <li>Email address</li>
              <li>Name (optional)</li>
              <li>Payment information (processed securely by our payment provider)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-terrain-800 mt-6 mb-3">GPX and Map Data</h3>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              When you use our service, we collect:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-terrain-700 space-y-2">
              <li>GPX files you upload containing trail routes and coordinates</li>
              <li>Map customization preferences and settings</li>
              <li>Points of interest you add to your maps</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-terrain-800 mt-6 mb-3">Usage Data</h3>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We automatically collect certain information when you use our service:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-terrain-700 space-y-2">
              <li>Device and browser information</li>
              <li>IP address and approximate location</li>
              <li>Pages visited and features used</li>
              <li>Time spent on pages and interaction patterns</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-terrain-900 mb-4">How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We use the information we collect to:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-terrain-700 space-y-2">
              <li>Provide, maintain, and improve our trail map creation service</li>
              <li>Process your transactions and manage your account</li>
              <li>Generate accurate terrain contours and points of interest for your maps</li>
              <li>Send you important updates about your account or our service</li>
              <li>Respond to your support requests and inquiries</li>
              <li>Analyze usage patterns to improve user experience</li>
              <li>Detect and prevent fraudulent or unauthorized activity</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-terrain-900 mb-4">Analytics and Tracking</h2>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We use PostHog for analytics to understand how users interact with our service.
              This helps us improve the product and user experience. Analytics data is processed
              in the European Union (Frankfurt). PostHog may collect:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-terrain-700 space-y-2">
              <li>Page views and navigation patterns</li>
              <li>Feature usage and button clicks</li>
              <li>Session duration and engagement metrics</li>
              <li>Device and browser characteristics</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
              You can opt out of analytics tracking using the cookie consent banner when you
              first visit our site, or by updating your preferences via the "Cookie Settings"
              link in the footer at any time.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-terrain-900 mb-4">Customer Support</h2>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed">
              We use Intercom to provide customer support. When you interact with our support
              chat, Intercom may collect your email, conversation history, and device information
              to help us assist you better. This data is subject to Intercom's privacy policy.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-terrain-900 mb-4">Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Our service integrates with third-party services to provide core functionality:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-terrain-700 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>OpenStreetMap:</strong> Geographic data for maps and points of interest</li>
              <li><strong>Google Gemini:</strong> AI-powered point of interest suggestions</li>
              <li><strong>Payment processors:</strong> Secure handling of payment transactions</li>
              <li><strong>Cloud hosting providers:</strong> Secure storage and delivery of our service</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
              These services have their own privacy policies governing their data practices.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-terrain-900 mb-4">Data Security</h2>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed">
              We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect
              your personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or
              destruction. This includes encryption in transit and at rest, regular security
              assessments, and access controls.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-terrain-900 mb-4">Data Retention</h2>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed">
              We retain your personal information for as long as your account is active or as
              needed to provide you services. You can request deletion of your account and
              associated data at any time by contacting us. Some information may be retained
              as required by law or for legitimate business purposes.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-terrain-900 mb-4">Your Rights</h2>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal data:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-terrain-700 space-y-2">
              <li>Access the personal information we hold about you</li>
              <li>Correct inaccurate or incomplete information</li>
              <li>Request deletion of your personal data</li>
              <li>Object to or restrict processing of your data</li>
              <li>Data portability (receive your data in a portable format)</li>
              <li>Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
              To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the details below.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-terrain-900 mb-4">Cookies</h2>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We use cookies and similar technologies to maintain your session, remember your
              preferences, and analyze usage patterns. When you first visit our site, you will
              see a cookie consent banner where you can choose which types of cookies to accept.
            </p>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We use the following categories of cookies:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-terrain-700 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>Essential:</strong> Required for the site to function (e.g., consent preferences)</li>
              <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Help us understand how visitors use our site (PostHog)</li>
              <li><strong>Marketing:</strong> Enable customer support chat functionality (Intercom)</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
              You can update your cookie preferences at any time using the "Cookie Settings" link
              in the footer. Note that cookies are shared between www.topostory.com and
              app.topostory.com to provide a seamless experience across our services.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-terrain-900 mb-4">Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed">
              TopoStory is not intended for children under 16 years of age. We do not knowingly
              collect personal information from children. If you believe we have collected
              information from a child, please contact us immediately.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-terrain-900 mb-4">Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed">
              We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any
              material changes by posting the new policy on this page and updating the
              "Last updated" date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-terrain-900 mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
            <p class="text-terrain-700 leading-relaxed">
              If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please
              contact us through our support chat or email us at privacy@topostory.com.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
